  issues, including critical security vulnerabilities, functional bugs, and
  failing Vercel deployments. The process involved systematically addressing
  each problem: implementing secure HMAC-based session management compatible
  with Vercel's Edge Runtime, adding robust input validation and pagination to
  API routes, correcting PDF generation logic for accurate sleep metrics, and
  enhancing form field behavior. A significant portion of the effort was
  dedicated to resolving persistent Vercel deployment failures. This required
  updating Next.js to address a critical security vulnerability
  (CVE-2025-66478), migrating ESLint to a new configuration format, and
  ultimately refactoring the Prisma client initialization to be lazy-loaded,
  preventing build-time database connection errors. After several iterations of
  fixes and debugging, all Vercel deployments are now successfully passing."
